      • rstoolbox.io.read_fasta

rstoolbox.io.read_fasta¶

rstoolbox.io.read_fasta(filename, expand=False, multi=False, defchain='A')¶

Reads one or more FASTA files and returns the appropiate object containing the requested data: the DesignFrame.

The default generated DesignFrame will contain two columns:

Column Name Data Content
description Sequence identifier.
sequence_<chain> Sequence content.

The sequence column assigned as sequence_A is an arbitrary decision that has to do compatibility issues with the rest of functions and methods of DesignFrame.

In [1]: from rstoolbox.io import read_fasta
   ...: import pandas as pd
   ...: pd.set_option('display.width', 1000)
   ...: pd.set_option('display.max_columns', 500)
   ...: df = read_fasta("../rstoolbox/tests/data/*fa$", multi=True)
   ...: df
   ...:

Note

Notice everything from the original description after the | symbol is lost after that process.

Parameters:
  • filename (str) – file name or file pattern to search.
  • expand (bool) – Try to better associate sequence ID if format is PDB FASTA.
  • multi (bool) – When True, indicates that data is readed from multiple files.
  • defchain (str) – Default chain to use. If not provided that is ‘A’.
Returns:

DesignFrame.
Raises:
IOError:if filename cannot be found.
